# Next.js 16 App Router

## File conventions
- App Router only. No Pages Router patterns.
- Default exports only for `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`,
  `not-found.tsx`, `template.tsx`, `default.tsx`, `route.ts`, and `proxy.ts`.
  Everywhere else: named exports.
- Files: kebab-case. Components: PascalCase identifier inside the file.
- All internal links via `next/link`. All images via `next/image` with explicit
  `width`, `height`, `alt`. Prefer WebP and lazy loading.
- In Next.js 16 the proxy file is `proxy.ts` (not `middleware.ts`). The exported
  function must be named `proxy` (not `middleware`).

## Server vs Client Components
- Server by default. Add `'use client'` ONLY for: event handlers, useState/useEffect/
  useReducer/useContext, browser-only APIs (window, localStorage, IndexedDB),
  or libraries that require the client runtime.
- Push `'use client'` AS DEEP AS POSSIBLE. Wrap the smallest interactive leaf;
  keep parents server.
- Never `'use client'` for data fetching or for state the server can own.
- Add `import 'server-only'` at the top of any module that uses secrets, the
  Supabase service-role client, or DB internals.

## Data fetching
- Fetch in Server Components with native `fetch()` and explicit cache options:
  `{ cache: 'force-cache' | 'no-store' }` or `{ next: { revalidate, tags } }`.
- Co-locate fetches with the component that uses them; do not lift to layouts
  for sharing — use React `cache()` to dedupe within a render.
- Cross-request memoization: `unstable_cache(fn, keyParts, { tags, revalidate })`.
  Always provide explicit `tags`.
- Mutations invalidate via `revalidatePath()` / `revalidateTag()` from a Server
  Action — never from Client Components.
- NEVER `useEffect` for data fetching.

## Server Actions
- All form submissions and mutations go through Server Actions (`'use server'`).
- Validate every input with Zod before touching the database.
- Model expected errors as return values: `{ ok: false, error: '...' }`. Use
  `useActionState` + `react-hook-form` for forms. Reserve try/catch for
  unexpected errors.
- After success: `revalidatePath`/`revalidateTag` and/or `redirect()` — never
  manually mutate client cache.

## Route handlers
- `app/api/**/route.ts`, named HTTP-verb exports, `NextRequest`/`NextResponse`.
- Validate body and params with Zod. Return `NextResponse.json(data, { status })`.
- Set `export const runtime` and `export const dynamic` explicitly when behavior
  depends on them.

## loading.tsx, error.tsx, not-found.tsx (companion files)
- Every route segment that fetches MUST have a colocated `loading.tsx` (skeleton
  matching the page layout, not a spinner) and an `error.tsx` (`'use client'`,
  receives `error` and `reset` props, renders a retry button).
- Use `not-found.tsx` plus `notFound()` from `next/navigation` for 404s.

## Metadata
- Use the Metadata API: static `metadata` or async `generateMetadata`. Never
  `next/head`. Provide `title.template`, `openGraph`, `twitter`, `robots` in
  the root layout.
- Export `viewport` as a separate const (Next.js 16 splits it from metadata).

## Proxy (formerly Middleware)
- One `proxy.ts` at the project root. Keep it thin: auth refresh, redirects.
  No data fetching or heavy work.
- Matcher MUST exclude static assets:
  `'/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico|icons|manifest.json|sw.js|workbox-.*|.*\\.(?:svg|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|webp)$).*)'`
